<p><b>War</b> is an armed conflict<sup id=3D"cite_ref-2" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-2"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>a<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> betw=
een the armed forces of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_(pol=
ity)" title=3D"State (polity)">states</a>, or between <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government" title=3D"Government">governmental</a> force=
s and armed groups that are organized under a certain command structure and=
 have the capacity to sustain <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mili=
tary_operation" title=3D"Military operation">military operations</a>, or be=
tween such organized groups.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-3" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-3"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p><p>It is generally characterized by widespread <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Violence" title=3D"Violence">violence</a>, destruction, an=
d mortality, using <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_army" t=
itle=3D"Regular army">regular</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Irregular_military" title=3D"Irregular military">irregular</a> <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military" title=3D"Military">military for=
ces</a>. <b>Warfare</b> refers to the common activities and characteristics=
 of types of war, or of wars in general.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-4"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>=20
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Total_war" title=3D"Total w=
ar">Total war</a> is warfare that is not restricted to purely <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legitimate_military_target" title=3D"Legitimate=
 military target">legitimate military targets</a>, and can result in massiv=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian_casualty" title=3D"Civi=
lian casualty">civilian</a> or other <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Non-combatant" title=3D"Non-combatant">non-combatant</a> suffering and <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casualty_(person)" title=3D"Casualt=
y (person)">casualties</a>.
</p>
