<p>In <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coercion,_Capital,_and_Eu=
ropean_States,_AD_990%E2%80%931992" title=3D"Coercion, Capital, and Europea=
n States, AD 990=E2=80=931992">Coercion, Capital, and European States, AD 9=
90=E2=80=931992</a></i>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_T=
illy" title=3D"Charles Tilly">Charles Tilly</a>, professor of history, soci=
ology, and social science at the University of Michigan and Columbia Univer=
sity, and described as "the founding father of 21st-century sociology,"<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-30" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/War#cite_note-30"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>29<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> argued that "war made the state, and t=
he state made war", saying that wars have led to creation of states which i=
n their turn perpetuate war.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-31" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-31"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>30<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-32" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/War#cite_note-32"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>31<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Tilly's theory of state formation is consi=
dered dominant in the state formation literature.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:7_33-=
0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_no=
te-:7-33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-34" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-34"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-35" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#c=
ite_note-35"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Abrams_in_formation.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-des=
cription"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/=
