<p>Estimates for total deaths due to war vary widely. In one estimate, prim=
itive warfare from 50,000 to 3000 BCE has been thought to have claimed 400<=
span class=3D"nowrap">&nbsp;</span>million=C2=B1133,000 victims based on th=
e assumption that it accounted for the 15.1% of all deaths.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-58" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#ci=
te_note-58"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>57<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ian_Morris=
_(historian)" title=3D"Ian Morris (historian)">Ian Morris</a> estimated tha=
t the rate could be as high as 20%.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-59" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-59"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>58<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 Other scholars find the prehistoric percentage much lower, around 2%, simi=
lar to the Neanderthals and ancestors of apes and primates.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-60" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#ci=
te_note-60"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>59<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p><p>For the period 3000 BCE until 1991, estimates range from 151<span cl=
ass=3D"nowrap">&nbsp;</span>million<sup id=3D"cite_ref-61" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-61"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>60<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 to several<span class=3D"nowrap">&nbsp;</span>billion.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
62" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_n=
ote-62"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>61<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-63" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-63"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>62<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The lowest estim=
ate for history of 151 million was calculated by William Eckhardt. He expla=
ined his method as summing the recorded casualties and multiplying their av=
erage by the number of recorded battles or wars. This method excludes indir=
ect deaths for premodern wars and all deaths for unrecorded wars. Few premo=
dern wars were recorded beyond Eurasia and only 18 wars were recorded for p=
eriod 3000 - 1500 BC worldwide.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-64" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-64"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>63<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Late=
r researchers shifted from Eckhardt's approach to general estimations of th=
e percentage of population killed by wars. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Azar_Gat" title=3D"Azar Gat">Azar Gat</a> and <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ian_Morris_(historian)" title=3D"Ian Morris (historian=
)">Ian Morris</a> both give the lowest estimate of 1% for history including=
 all the 20th century,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-65" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-65"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>64<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-66" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wa=
r#cite_note-66"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>65<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-67" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-67"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>66<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> or about=
 1 billion.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-68" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-68"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>67<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The highest estimates of=
 both scholars exceed the famous "hoax" of 3,640,000,000 people killed in w=
ars which circulated decades in scholarly literature in various countries.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-69" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/War#cite_note-69"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>68<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Gat gives 5%,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-70"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note=
-70"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>69<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> or about 5 billion.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-71" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-71"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>70<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 Morris gives for the 20th century 2%, for 1400-1900 3% in Europe and "slig=
htly higher" elsewhere, 5% for the ancient empires in 500 BC - AD 200, 10% =
for the rest of history and 20% for prehistory.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-72" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-72">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>71<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-73" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-73"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>72<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> His total for history is=
 thus about 9 billion.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-74" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-74"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>73<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Largest_wars_by_death_toll"=
>Largest wars by death toll</h3></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_wars_by_deat=
h_toll" title=3D"List of wars by death toll">List of wars by death toll</a>=
</div>
<p>The deadliest war in history, in terms of the cumulative number of death=
s since its start, is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II=
" title=3D"World War II">World War II</a>, from 1939 to 1945, with 70=E2=80=
=9385&nbsp;million deaths, followed by the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Mongol_conquests" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Mongol conquests"=
>Mongol conquests</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-75" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-75"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>74<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> at up to 60&nb=
sp;million. As concerns a belligerent's losses in proportion to its prewar =
population, the most destructive war in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Modern_history" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Modern history">modern=
 history</a> may have been the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Par=
aguayan_War" title=3D"Paraguayan War">Paraguayan War</a> (see <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paraguayan_War_casualties" title=3D"Paraguayan =
War casualties">Paraguayan War casualties</a>). War resulted in 31,000 deat=
hs in 2013, down from 72,000 deaths in 1990.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-GDB2013_76-=
0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_no=
te-GDB2013-76"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>75<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p><p>War usually results in significant deterioration of infrastructure a=
nd the ecosystem, a decrease in social spending, <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Famine" title=3D"Famine">famine</a>, large-scale emigration =
from the war zone, and often the mistreatment of <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Prisoner_of_war" title=3D"Prisoner of war">prisoners of war<=
/a> or civilians.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-77" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-77"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>76<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-78" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_=
note-78"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>77<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-79" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-79"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>78<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For instance, o=
f the nine million people who were on the territory of the <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byelorussian_Soviet_Socialist_Republic" title=3D"B=
yelorussian Soviet Socialist Republic">Byelorussian SSR</a> in 1941, some 1=
.6&nbsp;million were killed by the Germans in actions away from battlefield=
s, including about 700,000 prisoners of war, 500,000 Jews, and 320,000 peop=
le counted as partisans (the vast majority of whom were unarmed civilians).=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-80" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/War#cite_note-80"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>79<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Another byproduct of some wars is t=
he prevalence of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propaganda" title=
=3D"Propaganda">propaganda</a> by some or all parties in the conflict,<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-81" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/War#cite_note-81"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>80<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and increased revenues by <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weapons_manufacturers" class=3D"mw-redirect" t=
itle=3D"Weapons manufacturers">weapons manufacturers</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-82" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War#cite=
_note-82"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>81<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Three of the ten most costly wars, in terms of loss of life, have be=
en waged in the last century. These are the two World Wars, followed by the=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Sino-Japanese_War" title=
=3D"Second Sino-Japanese War">Second Sino-Japanese War</a> (which is someti=
mes considered part of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_I=
I" title=3D"World War II">World War II</a>, or as overlapping). Most of the=
 others involved China or neighboring peoples. The death toll of World War =
II, being over 60&nbsp;million, surpasses all other war-death-tolls.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-users.erols_83-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/War#cite_note-users.erols-83"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>82<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
